Politics of the now famous handshake between president Uhuru Kenyatta and his nemesis Raila Odinga dominated the burial of mzee Peter Musyoka, father to national super alliance co principal and Wiper leader Kalonzo Musyoka, even as a section of legislators  from Ukambani region claimed they had been  left out However National Assembly majority leader Aden Duale dismissed the claims insisting the country has moved on, with the  Senate minority leader James Orengo saying no one can ignore what has taken place in the country to date. This as President Uhuru Kenyatta  dismissed claims by a section of leaders that the government was borrowing too much.  